         <div>
            <head>THE NEGRO SPEAKS OF RIVERS</head>
            
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">I’ve known rivers . . .</l>
               <l enjamb="no">I’ve known rivers ancient as the world and older than the flow</l>
               <l enjamb="no">of human blood in human veins.</l>
               <l enjamb="no">My soul has grown deep like the rivers.</l>
            </lg>
            
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">I bathed in the <placeName>Euphrates</placeName> when dawns were young,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">I built my hut near the <placeName>Congo</placeName> and it lulled me to sleep,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">I looked upon the <placeName>Nile</placeName> and raised the pyramids above it.</l>
            </lg>
            
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">I heard the singing of the <placeName>Mississippi</placeName> when</l>
               <l enjamb="no"><name>Abe Lincoln</name> went down to <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">And I’ve seen its muddy bosom turn all golden in the sunset.</l> 
            </lg>
            
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">I’ve known rivers:</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Ancient, dusky rivers,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">My soul has grown deep like the rivers.</l>
            </lg>
            
            
            
            <byline>-Langston Hughes</byline>
         </div>
